    • MemorySegment

      public MemorySegment(long startPhysicalAddress, long startVirtualAddress, long size, byte[][] content)
      Create a new memory segment from an already existing 2D array.
      Parameter:
      startPhysicalAddress - The start address of the segment in physical memory.
      startVirtualAddress - The start address of the segment in virtual memory.
      size - The size of this segment.
      content - The contents to copy to this segment.

    • MemorySegment

      public MemorySegment(long startPhysicalAddress, long startVirtualAddress, long size, @NotNull @NotNull InputStream input) throws IOException
      Create a new segment which reads data from an Input Stream.
      Parameter:
      startPhysicalAddress - The start address of this segment in actual memory.
      startVirtualAddress - The start address of the segment in virtual memory.
      size - The size of this segment.
      input - The stream to write to this segment.
      Löst aus:
      IOException - If any read error occurs while reading.

    • getStartPhysicalAddress

      public long getStartPhysicalAddress()
      Returns the address where this segment starts in physical memory. If this is the same as the virtual address, this means QEMU does not resolve virtual addresses for the used architecture and this is not actually the physical address.
      Gibt zurück:
      The address where this segment starts.

    • getStartVirtualAddress

      public long getStartVirtualAddress()
      Returns the supposed virtual address. If this is the same value as the physical address, it means QEMU does not resolve virtual into physical addresses.
      Gibt zurück:
      The first virtual address of this segment.
